        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11538",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Alexander Veremyev wrote:\n{quote}Interesting idea is offered by Vincent - ZF-249\n\nI have tested it a bit with Latin (including umlauts) and Cyrillic letters.\nIt works properly on Linux and has some problems under Windows.\n{quote}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-11-13T17:03:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-11-13T17:03:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12359",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've tested offered solution under Linux\/Windows. It doesn't work correct for all cases.\n\nIssue is closed with current encoding management support and new utf-8 anslyzer.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-24T19:45:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-24T19:45:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/15757",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "preg_match() works as it expected if 'u' modifier is set at the end of pattern.\n\n{code}\n$c = '\u00f9';\necho preg_match('\/\\p{L}\/u', $c); \/\/ 1\n\n$c = '\u044b';\necho preg_match('\/\\p{L}\/u', $c); \/\/ 1\n\n$c = '!';\necho preg_match('\/\\p{L}\/u', $c); \/\/ 0\n{code}\n\nAccording to the [PCRE specification|http:\/\/www.pcre.org\/pcre.txt] '\/[\\p{L}\\p{N}]\/u' patter has to be used to match alpha-numeric characters.\n\nIt's definitely a way to implement complete UTF-8 analyzer.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexander",
                        "name": "alexander",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Veremyev",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-07-12T00:25:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-07-12T00:25:56.000+0000"
                },
